Ondo State Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu has approved the appointment of Mr. Oluwadare Aragbaiye as the new Head of Service of the state public service. In a statement signed by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Segun Ajiboye, the governor approved the appointment in line with the provisions of Section 208, Sub-section 3 of the Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria 1999, as amended. While congratulating the new Head of Service, Akeredolu, emphasized that the new Head of Service will provide the right leadership for the state public service and also complement the efforts of his administration in prepositioning the public service. Prior to his appointment as Head of Service, Aragbaiye was the Permanent Secretary, Government House and Protocol. Aragbaiye joined the state public service in 1985 as an Administrative Officer, Grade Level 08 in the Ministry of Finance and he has once served as Permanent Secretary in the Ministries of General Administration and Transport. The governor described the the new HoS as shrewd administrator who had traversed several MDAs in his career as a public servant. The new Head of Service will be sworn-in this week, according to Ajiboye. Lalong appoints acting HoS Bayelsa gets new Head of Service Tambuwal removes 2 perm secs loyal to Wamakko Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin